tall django-extra-settings</code></li>\n<li>Add <code>extra_settings</code> to <code>settings.INSTALLED_APPS</code></li>\n<li>Run <code>python manage.py migrate</code></li>\n<li>Run <code>python manage.py collectstatic</code></li>\n<li>Restart your application server</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<h3>Settings</h3>\n<p>All these settings are optional, if not defined in <code>settings.py</code> the default values (listed below) will be used.</p>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># if True the template tag will fallback to django.conf.settings,</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># very useful to retrieve conf settings such as DEBUG.</span>\n<span class=\"n\">EXTRA_SETTINGS_FALLBACK_TO_CONF_SETTINGS</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span>\n</pre>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># the upload_to path value of settings of type 'file'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">EXTRA_SETTINGS_FILE_UPLOAD_TO</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'files'</span>\n</pre>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># the upload_to path value of settings of type 'image'</span>\n<span class=\"n\">EXTRA_SETTINGS_IMAGE_UPLOAD_TO</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'images'</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>Templates</h3>\n<pre>{% load extra_settings %}\n\n{% get_setting 'SETTING_NAME' default='django-extra-settings' %}\n</pre>\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"c1\"># create python 3.7 virtual environment</span>\nvirtualenv testing_django_extra_settings -p <span class=\"s2\">\"python3.7\"</span> --no-site-packages\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># activate virtualenv</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">cd</span> testing_django_extra_settings <span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span> . bin/activate\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># clone repo</span>\ngit clone https://github.com/fabiocaccamo/django-extra-settings.git src <span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"nb\">cd</span> src\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># run tests</span>\npython setup.py <span class=\"nb\">test</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># or</span>\npython manage.py <span class=\"nb\">test</span> --settings <span class=\"s2\">\"tests.settings\"</span>\n</pre>\n<hr>\n<h2>License</h2>\n<p>Released under <a href=\"LICENSE.txt\" rel=\"nofollow\">MIT License</a>.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6623724, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9657278b0dcf9d35e903d4cee0409e1e", "sha256": "d6cc0347e7ccecdc371bca470f54257add91f02727952d26ae872ab90d8fc0ba"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "django_extra_settings-0.1.0-py2-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9657278b0dcf9d35e903d4cee0409e1e", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2", "requires_python": null, "size": 11562, "upload_time": "2020-02-13T11:58:03", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-13T11:58:03.653173Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/d2/48/f9c2e367d1561bae797649b061abeafd57288921a72e97612134fda81b40/django_extra_settings-0.1.0-py2-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "911ce693ef56f710c50f0e8122752800", "sha256": "1953a7dc619b0a9bb3a02863ff723d53bc7228453ea470ee405dba0853ac29bf"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "django-extra-settings-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "911ce693ef56f710c50f0e8122752800", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 9425, "upload_time": "2020-02-13T11:58:06", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-13T11:58:06.221687Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b4/5b/a7c68d19506c01e5ba443aee19244b7a60b9d10b575c53f6ce45de272b22/django-extra-settings-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3b751b396d8739d797db4bae08567977", "sha256": "e197ae18ea3a1e1c34e0c426324603c00657c6397edfaabc28584cf0683bac19"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "django_extra_settings-0.1.1-py2-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3b751b396d8739d797db4bae08567977", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py2", "requires_python": null, "size": 11489, "upload_time": "2020